ottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Mar 29th 4:04 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I'm new to EverQuest and new to being a Bard.&nbsp;&nbsp;It seems I've read somewhere that you can create a macro that would conceivably allow you to switch between your instrument and your weapon.  At this point, I cannot hold my drum in the secondary slot and my weapon in the primary slot (I believe the weapon takes up both primary and secondary). To move between the two involves opening my inventory and switching them out.  Is it possible to make a macro that would do that? and if so, what would it look like?<br><br>Thanks for any advice/help!!<br><br>Tremela<br>5th lvl Bard<br>The Seventh Hammer<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
	   </form></table><ul>
<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98594431367855></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98594431367855><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=4&mid=98594431367855>RE: Macros</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=4&mid=98594431367855#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Mar 30th 4:25 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hello! here is the way :)<br>First, get three open inventory slots (With no bags on those slots). <br>Have your weapons equipped, and put two instruments in the empty inventory slots. <br>Leave one of the slots empty. Now, go to a free hotkey page. An easy way to do this is by pressing shift+6, <br>which will take you to the sixth page. Move your mouse pointer to the "Melee 1" slot in your inventory screen. <br>Click and hold over the slot until the button pops up and is on your cursor. <br>Drag the cursor over to the first hotkey slot in the bottom left of your screen. <br>Position the cursor so the top left of the button is in the middle of the hotkey slot, <br>and click your mouse once to set that slot to Melee 1. Repeat this process for Melee 2, <br>the two instrument inventory slots, and the empty inventory slot. <br>You will now be able to switch easily between weapons and instruments, without going to the Persona screen. <br>Valaba<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
	   </form></table><ul>

</ul>
<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98591293656559></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98591293656559><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=4&mid=98591293656559>RE: Macros</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=4&mid=98591293656559#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=2568><span id= >philoscope</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>63 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Mar 29th 7:42 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[2.84]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>It's the other way around.&nbsp;&nbsp;Your instrument takes up both slots.  You can't do it with macros, but you can with hot-key slots.  Click and drag the slots from your inventory (it will take some changing of screens) into one of your hot-key banks.<br><br>The actual strategy involved I cannot think well enough to explain right now.  but I'm sure that there will be other posts to help with that.<br><br>Philo<br>&nbsp;<br>Looking for love.....pity there's so little in humanity.</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
