	   <tr><td colspan=2>I wouldn't worry about upgrading just yet.&nbsp;&nbsp;Obvious if the chance comes along, take it but at 6th level, there's absolutely no need to be wearing bronze.  My own bard went until level eight wearing a full set of patchwork (!) with a Lockjaw vest (AC12 and +5STA if memory serves) and almost never died camping goblins in Misty Thicket unless she got two yellows on her and didn't have the sense to Selo herself out of there before becoming too wounded.  Even now, she's in banded at level eight (only because my main is a master smith and made her a set of small banded) and is only wearing the AC15 banded tunic over the 12AC +5STA LJ vest because that leather tunic with a suit of banded looks stupid.<br><br>Before the world of Twinkdom we live in, it seemed that patchwork would get you to level 5 or 6, leather to 10, banded to about 15-20 and start getting plate armors (bronze, fine steel..etc) after that.  Now that every other character is getting started with a full suit of bronze or better, everyone feels like if they're in leather at level six they're some sort of second class citizen.  However, the truth is that the MOBs haven't gotten any more dangerous in EC since two years ago so don't worry about it.  You have a very nice tunic for your level and should think about upgrading to banded next (1pp per AC) and then bronze as you can afford it (2pp per AC) in terms of both money and weight.  I know as a wood elf bard, a full suit of bronze isn't in my future.  I doubt even a visible set of bronze is..<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
