<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98536026824038></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98536026824038><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=4&mid=98536026824038>RE: Bardic Frustration</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=4&mid=98536026824038#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Mar 23rd 10:11 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[2.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Sorry to contradict the last post, but bard's aren't a melee class past 16...We aren't a caster class either. Think about it this way (to the original poster), Bards, with hymn of Restoration, can wind up healing (by level 16) 12 points of damage, every 3 seconds to every member of the GROUP...meaning after 9 seconds you have wound up healing for (depending on group size) at least 72 points of healing if you are grouped with another person...108 hit points if 2 people are grouped with you...144 hit points if 3 people are grouped with you, culminating in 216 EVERY 9 seconds if you are grouped with 5 other people...Remember thats if you use a lute...Obviously thats only one song, of which you can sing 3 to 4...<br><br>What does this prove? A few things:<br><br>1. Group...your songs become additively better with each person you add, and have a geometrically increasing effect on efficiency...meaning each person you add, makes your group better by a VERY large multiple...(If you add one tank for example, using JUST the healing song shown above, you are basically getting 3, he is healing over 12 times as fast as normal, and can regain his total hit points over 3 times in battle without a healer)<br><br>2. After 16, when grouped, unless NO OTHER melee is grouped with you, use instruments instead of meleeing. This is what contradicts the previous poster...and if it contradicts other boards you have read, so be it...While we could melee, theoretically, I use the hit points to simply balance out the higher aggro we create and the more hits we get...We, in my opinion, are not meleers who can sing, we are singers who can melee. When grouped singing with an instrument doubles your effectiveness, and can (as the healing song shows) make your group 3 times as effective instead of just 2 times, or just being another melee. Use a lute when singing healing. Maybe switch to an instrument when singing Anthem, use a lute when singing lull for crowd control, or us a drum while singing Jig of vigor for long battles. Past level 16, sing using intruments when grouped, you will be a super-effective member of the team. <br><br>3. Don't cut yourself short. The effects of a bard on a group are subtle. You don't see the health bubble of the tank shoot up when you sing your song...but it WILL stay where it is longer than usual. Anthem's haste and str buff are really visible when you are in a melee heavy group...(Real life example: It took a group consisting of me a warrior a cleric 2 druids and a warrior about 5 minutes to kill an Aviak Avocet at level 16...When i sang Anthem in a group of myself, a warrior, a ranger, a monk, a rogue and a cleric, it took us 1 minute. While this is disproportionate because of the fact that druids can't blast an avocet at that level (Avocets are too high), the damage output of tanks normally wouldn't be that high anyway) And group lull can sometimes save that poor healer who has inadvertently aggroed some of the extra mobs with the his heals. Selo can save your group if you don't have SoW. Jaxon's Jig can replenish the stamina of your tanks during an extra long fight. In effect, you can be one the best additions to your group, especially if you don't happen to be grouped with a Shaman, Enchanter, AND Cleric (which is the only combination which would give you each buff available from a bard).<br><br>Last piece I ought to mention is that Bard's can easily duel any number of melee's against you, and can duel most casters (depending on ability). We can also Kite and thereby solo, ANY pure melee in the game, given enough space, and enough patience.<br><br>Just my 2 cp <br>Happy hunting :)<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
