	   <tr><td colspan=2>Well its really depends on the situation what you will do. If you groups lack melee. Go melee. If you group lags casters you might go instrumental.<br><br>Though i wouldnt advice doing heal songs in battle at higher level since it creates alot of hate towards mobs (18*6 hps) each 6 second. So if you have no crowd control chances are that you are gonna get beaten up by an add.<br><br>Another role of a bard is small crowd control. If you learn how to use charm efficent it would aid your group alot. Or if you get two mobs or an add you can keep one mezzed until the other is dead. Again depends on the group if you should use charm or mez<br><br>A few piece of advice though. Never play aoe songs in dungeons.<br><br>If you charm or mez a mob you can be very sure hell come wack ya butt when he get outta charm/mez<br><br>Play mana song in each moment you are not fighting<br>If casters are lom just play mana song while meleeing.<br><br>My 2 cents<br>&nbsp;<br>Cyrix<br>60 Bard<br>Test</td></tr>
