<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98530567310983></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98530567310983><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=4&mid=98530567310983>RE: I'm a new bard and so far so good, but . . .</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=4&mid=98530567310983#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=31993><span id=Scholar>Taamas</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>63 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Mar 22nd 7:01 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.33]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>*long post, proceed with caution*<br><br>well after you hit 20 basically your whole life changes. Usually bards can tank most monsters becuz they don't hit very hard compared to our hps. but when you hit 20, everything changes and monsters hit for insane amounts compared to our hps. i have 600 some hps and im lvl 26. a lvl 20, or even lower, barb war has more hps than me! its pathetic that you can't live that long, thats why its almost imperative that you have some kind of healer (druid/shammy/cleric). also at least 2 tanks to fight in front of you, also to taunt off of you, in the rare case when you want to melee is great. sometimes i feel like meleeing, although i can do more dmg wit my instruments, DoT, healing, haste and mana songs. its basically this: all melee types out dmg you, plain and simple. so if you increase their abilities to output dmg (haste songs) and keep them alive longer to deal more dmg (HoR) they will be able to do your dmg AND theirs witout any songs if you were meleeing. <br><br>so when you hit 20, you should mainly be using instruments and playing your much underestimated songs (lvl 20 mana song, regains mana FASTER than breeze). now add in HoR wit lute or mandolin (insane regen during a battle), haste songs, and your ever-painful DoTs (whether its CoD or DDD) your doing as much good there than you are singing and meleeing. it might seem like it doesn't do much (especially the DoTs and haste) but when you grow up, you'll notice the change in the dmg output. now for the casters, you should twist whichever rhytmn is appropriate, healing and haste songs. the casters don't have the hps like the others, so the tanks can massacre them easy enuff wit haste, and healing + resist rythmns to keep em alive from those annoying spells. (ex. sarnak adherant cast an annoying poison-based, it seems, AE DD which takes everyone within range down to 2 bubs or so. i hate that spell, don't know the name tho) <br><br>so basically to sum it up, melee almost all the time till bout 20, then switch to your powerful instrument-based songs. i have much fun wit my bard, although he currently has 2 pieces of lambent rest is fine plate, and i still haven't got the mask!&nbsp;&nbsp;=(  anyways have fun, hope i helped a bit.<br><br>Taamas Starsinger<br>26th Bard<br>Saryrn<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
